  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Disaster Risk Reduction and Fostering Social Cohesion Among Communities Affected by Refugee Influx</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM implements a range of activities aimed at strengthening and enhancing the disaster risk reduction capacities and social cohesion of both the population and government institutions in Bangladesh, which will increase resilience and disaster risk management. The initiatives will include measures to prevent or mitigate disaster risks as well as strengthen preparedness for the benefit of both refugees and host communities. Such measures are particularly urgent in view of the approaching cyclone and monsoon season, which, unless urgent and immediate action is taken, will result in flooding and landslides.</narrative>
  </description>
